HEADWORD: Acanthaceous
<hw>Ac"an*tha"ceous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Armed with prickles, as a plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or resembling,
the family of plants of which the acanthus is the type.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 10 --></p>

<p><ent>Acanthine</ent>⟦br⟧
